post_text: Starting Monday, September 14th all West Delaware students will receive free breakfast and lunch. The USDA has recently extended the Summer Food Service Program until December 31st or until funds run out. At this point, no one really knows when this funding may run out, so like everything related to COVID, it will be a fluid process and we will notify families as soon as possible of any changes. Once the funds run out we will go back to the National School Breakfast and Lunch programs and students will be charged according to their eligibility.

post_text:
If you feel you haven‚Äôt gotten calls to different numbers, or would like to see which phone and email addresses we have you can do so in PowerSchool. There are 2 steps to verifying how you are called.

First Step: In PowerSchool in Eregistration. Many would have found this screen, but not all might have updated. It has lists for phone numbers for phone calls, phone numbers for texts and emails. Make sure this is up to date. Once updated it is approved by secretaries then overnight it moves to SchoolMessenger where phone calls are made.

Second Step: The following day as it takes overnight before new numbers show up in SchoolMessenger (or if you don‚Äôt see a difference check back the next day too) go to PowerSchool and then to SchoolMessenger on the left. It shows you the different types of phone calls the district makes and different numbers. Click on each type of call and choose how you want to receive the message.

If you put numbers in to receive texts you will also need to text the word ‚ÄúYes‚Äù to 67587

post_text:
Last night West Delaware (21-4) took on Washington (10-18) in the Class 4A regional final, winning 8-2.

Heather Heims (11) said the team is taking several extra precautions like disinfecting all equipment in between uses, sanitizing hands before water breaks, and limiting the number of people they expose themselves to to help keep them safe.

‚ÄúWhen the season first started we were all scared of how we could have our season ended anytime,‚Äù Heims said. ‚ÄúWe kept telling ourselves that we needed to play and give every game our all because we could be done at any second.‚Äù

West Delaware is on a 15 game winning streak heading into the state tournament on Monday in Fort Dodge.

Thank you to everyone who has already completed the Resource and Needs survey. If you have not, please consider doing this today. West Delaware is using this information in their planning to make sure all families and students get the support they need to be successful in the next school year, and we need to hear your voice!

If you have more than one student in a specific building, please just answer one survey for that building. If you have students in more than one building it would be helpful to fill out a survey for each building you have a student. Thank you for sharing your feedback with us.

High School Survey - https://forms.gle/f1ZczGm9tcLEotkP8

Middle School Survey - https://forms.gle/Lu3Ww1GSJTsgY7u69

Lambert Survey - https://forms.gle/yvA8qDkVYHeDAKh98

Students in middle school and high school were also emailed surveys and if possible it would be great for them to log on and complete those surveys as well.

shared_text:
West Delaware Soccer
May 23 at 5:36 PM ¬∑

Our final senior is Gracie Weeks! Congratulations 2020 Graduate!

Gracie is the daughter of Barry and Karole Weeks and she was a 4 year member of the girls soccer team. She was also involved in cross country, show choir, speech and speech captain, student council, dance marathon committee and National Honor Society.

In the fall, Gracie plans to attend the University of Iowa to study biochemistry on the pre-med track.

Gracie's favorite soccer memory was scoring her first goal, sophomore year, in the game against Vinton.

Thank you Gracie for the dedication and passion you gave to the WD Soccer program and the best of luck in the next chapter of your life! You will do great things!
photo credit: Leta Anderson

post_text:
A reminder that breakfast and lunch will be available to all children under the age of 18, regardless of whether they are West Delaware students or not. All we need is the number of students who are taking lunch. We do not need school ID or any verification of need.

Breakfast and lunch can both picked up at same time. Children can pick up grab and go meals from any of our district buildings. They will be required to take the meal with them and not stay on site to eat.

Meals can be picked up from 7:30-12:30 every weekday beginning Tuesday, March 17.

Beginning Thursday March 19th, we will have meals available at the same times at the following locations:
Ryan City Hall
Greeley Fire Station
Dundee Fire Station
Masonville Fire Station

post_text:
West Delaware Middle School
ARRIVAL TIME/PROCEDURE

Middle school staff is not expected to arrive to school until 7:45 AM. For this reason, the Middle School entrances will remain locked until 7:45 AM. At this time all Middle School students will be expected to enter the main (North-West) entrance of the building and be seated in the main gym,
on the bleachers or on the floor. Students desiring breakfast at this time, may go to the breakfast area; students choosing to eat breakfast at this time are expected to follow the lunchroom expectations. When entering the building, as a show of respect, please remove caps, and use a soft conversational voice.

Students will be permitted to enter the classrooms and locker areas at the 7:55 AM bell. Through-out the school year, a number of school activities are scheduled before 7:45 AM. Students participating in these activities should be with their sponsor until 7:45 AM.

post_text:
Would you like to be a Keystone AEA Board Member?
The Board of Directors is the governing body of the Agency, making equitable special education, media, and other educational services available to schools.

The Board's business is conducted openly, promoting communications with the public, and through the administrator, with Agency personnel.

Elections are for four-year terms or the unexpired portion of a term in the event of a vacancy. The Board meets monthly. Four-member, standing committees on Policy, Accreditation, Personnel, and Operations are appointed and meet throughout the year.
